.TH Install-Dependencies 1 "November 2025" "Install-Dependencies" "bin"
.SH NAME
Install-Dependencies \- Install required dependencies for docker-webhook
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Install-Dependencies
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Install-Dependencies
installs the required dependencies for the docker-webhook project on the host system.
This includes package managers (Homebrew or MacPorts on macOS), Docker, and other
prerequisites needed to build and run the docker-webhook container.
.PP
On macOS, it detects and uses the available package manager. On Linux, it uses
apt or yum/dnf depending on the distribution.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The script exits with status 0 on success, or 1 on error (e.g., unsupported OS,
missing package manager, or installation failure).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR brew (1),
.BR port (1),
.BR docker (1),
.BR apt (1),
.BR yum (1)
